---
export const prerender = true;
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { buildBreadcrumbJsonLd } from '../lib/seo';
import { getAllTools } from '@toolorbit/tool-registry';

const totalTools = getAllTools().length;
const breadcrumb = buildBreadcrumbJsonLd([
  { name: 'Home', path: '/' },
  { name: 'About', path: '/about' },
]);

const personJsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Person',
  name: 'Tanvirul Gani Oyon',
  url: 'https://toolorbit.xyz/about',
  description: 'Solo developer from Bangladesh, BSc Computer Science 2024. Building ToolOrbit.',
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About ToolOrbit - Built by a Solo Developer"
  description={`ToolOrbit is a collection of ${totalTools}+ free browser-based tools built by Tanvirul Gani Oyon, a solo developer from Bangladesh.`}
  canonicalPath="/about"
  jsonLd={[breadcrumb, personJsonLd]}
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6">
    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl font-bold text-base-50 mb-6">About ToolOrbit</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none prose-headings:font-display prose-headings:text-base-50 prose-p:text-base-300 prose-a:text-interactive prose-strong:text-base-100">

      <p>ToolOrbit is a collection of {totalTools} free, browser-based tools for developers, students, and anyone who works with files and text. Every tool on this site runs entirely inside your browser - your files and data are processed locally, never uploaded to a server.</p>

      <h2>Who built this</h2>
      <p>I'm <strong>Tanvirul Gani Oyon</strong>, a solo developer from Bangladesh. I completed my BSc in Computer Science in 2024 and I'm currently doing a postgraduate program in cybersecurity alongside building and maintaining web projects independently.</p>
      <p>I built ToolOrbit because I was tired of PDF and image tools that upload sensitive files to unknown servers, add watermarks to free outputs, or force you to create an account just to compress an image. Every tool here is genuinely free, genuinely client-side, and genuinely useful.</p>

      <h2>Why everything runs in your browser</h2>
      <p>Client-side processing is not a workaround - it's a better architecture for this class of tool. When your PDF is processed in your own browser tab, it never crosses a network connection to my server. This means:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your files are never stored, logged, or accessible to anyone other than you</li>
        <li>Processing is instant - no upload progress bar, no server queue</li>
        <li>There's no rate limit, because there's no server compute to protect</li>
        <li>The site scales to any traffic level without infrastructure costs</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Stack</h2>
      <p>ToolOrbit is built with <strong>Astro 6</strong> (static site generation with React islands), <strong>Cloudflare Pages</strong> for hosting (zero-cost CDN delivery), <strong>Cloudflare D1</strong> for the account database, and <strong>Better Auth</strong> for authentication. The client-side file processing uses <strong>pdf-lib</strong>, <strong>PDF.js</strong>, and the browser's native Canvas and Web Crypto APIs.</p>

      <h2>Reliability</h2>
      <p>Because tool pages are prerendered static HTML served from Cloudflare's global CDN, they load near-instantly regardless of your location. There's no application server that can go down. The only SSR routes are the dashboard and auth endpoints, which handle account data.</p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Found a bug? Have a tool suggestion? I read every message. Use the <a href="/contact">contact page</a> or email me at <a href="mailto:tanviroyon001@gmail.com">tanviroyon001@gmail.com</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
